    {
      "question": "A CFE is conducting a covert operation to identify potential theft of proprietary information by an employee suspected of sharing trade secrets with a competitor. The CFE plans to create a fictitious job opportunity at the competitor company and contact the suspect using a false identity to elicit information about stolen data. Which of the following is the PRIMARY ethical concern the CFE should address before proceeding?",
      "options": [
        "Whether the fictitious identity involves creating fake credentials or professional licenses",
