    {
      "question": "A private investigator is hired to conduct undercover work at a retail business suspected of insurance fraud. The investigator poses as a customer and secretly records conversations with employees about staged theft claims. Which of the following best describes the legal and ethical considerations the investigator must address?",
      "options": {
        "A": "The investigator may record conversations without consent as long as they are in a public retail space",
        "B": "The investigator must consider one-party consent laws, privacy expectations, pretext limitations, and potential trespass issues",
