    {
      "question": "A Certified Fraud Examiner is conducting a covert investigation into suspected procurement fraud at a manufacturing company. The CFE creates a fictitious vendor identity and submits false invoices to test whether the procurement manager will approve payments without proper verification, as alleged by a whistleblower. The CFE does not actually intend to collect any payments. Which of the following BEST describes the ethical and professional concerns with this approach?",
      "options": [
        "This approach is acceptable because no actual financial loss will occur and it directly tests the control weakness",
        "This approach is problematic because it involves the CFE creating false documents and actively participating in a fraudulent scheme, which could constitute entrapment or illegal conduct",
