    {
      "question": "A CFE is hired to conduct a covert investigation of suspected kickback schemes involving a company's purchasing manager. The CFE creates a fictitious supplier company and submits fraudulent bids to test whether the purchasing manager will accept bribes. During the investigation, the purchasing manager accepts $5,000 in cash and awards the contract to the fictitious company. Which of the following BEST describes the ethical and legal concerns with this investigative approach?",
      "options": [
        "This approach is acceptable because it successfully gathered evidence of the manager's willingness to accept bribes",
        "The CFE may have engaged in entrapment and created liability for the hiring company by initiating the criminal conduct",
